<TITLE> PM renews world peace pledge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 29 (bdnews24.com)  Sheikh Hasina has renewed Bangladesh's pledge to support global peace efforts as the leading provider of frontline peacekeepers. "We are always ready to help keep peace in any country in any part of the world under the UN Security Council," the prime minister told an International Day of UN Peacekeepers ceremony in Dhaka on Saturday. The UN Resident Coordinator paid tribute to Bangladeshi peacekeepers and offered "profound and humble condolences" for the 98 who died in the last 20 years. The prime minister was flanked on the podium by Ambassador at large M Ziauddin, the chiefs of three services and the Inspector General of Police. Ziauddin and Gen Abdul Mubin also spoke at the symbolic ceremony attended by ministers and senior officials. The prime minister watched a live cultural show and handed over crests to the widows of four servicemen who died in the past year and to those who sustained injuries in the line of duty on UN peace missi
